  <div class="topic">
    <h4>Download It! Or not!</h4>
    <p>First of all, it must be said that since you've already created your own framework, learning bootstrap should be a breeze. Espcially since much of the code you wrote for your framework is actually bootstrap source code.</p>

    <p>In any case, we first have to figure out how to get bootstrap into our app. For that we'll consult Bootstrap's website. Click <a href="http://getbootstrap.com/" target="_blank">here</a> to head to there.</p>

    <p>Head to the <a href="http://getbootstrap.com/getting-started/" target="_blank">getting started</a> page. There are about a million ways to get Bootstrap into your page: everything from downloading all the source code and putting in your, to simply copy/pasting a url or two into your page.</p>

    <p>Let's take the easiest route and just add the link from the CDN (basically cloud hosted). Copy/paste the following link tag and put it inside your <c>head</c> tag below where you included your <c>style.css</c>.</p>

    <pre style="background:#000;color:#f8f8f8"><span style="color:#e0c589">&lt;<span style="color:#e0c589">link</span> <span style="color:#e0c589">rel</span>=<span style="color:#65b042">"stylesheet"</span> <span style="color:#e0c589">href</span>=<span style="color:#65b042">"https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.6/css/bootstrap.min.css"</span> <span style="color:#e0c589">integrity</span>=<span style="color:#65b042">"sha384-1q8mTJOASx8j1Au+a5WDVnPi2lkFfwwEAa8hDDdjZlpLegxhjVME1fgjWPGmkzs7"</span> <span style="color:#e0c589">crossorigin</span>=<span style="color:#65b042">"anonymous"</span>></span>
</pre>
