  <div class="topic">
    <h4>The Nav Layout</h4>
    <p>Awesome, we're now ready to use it. First, let's implement the navbar. Bootstrap provides us with some code for generic navbars so we don't have to mess with it. It's located <a href="http://getbootstrap.com/components/#navbar" target="_blank">here</a> in the docs.</p>

    <p>Here we find several examples. Let's start slow by adding a default navbar. Add the following code to the top of your <c>body</c> tag:</p>
    <pre style="background:#000;color:#f8f8f8"><span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;<span style="color:#89bdff">nav</span> <span style="color:#89bdff">class</span>=<span style="color:#65b042">"navbar navbar-default"</span>></span>
<span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;/<span style="color:#89bdff">nav</span>></span>
</pre>

    <p>We want our navbar to be fixed to the top. Luckily, Bootstrap though of that. We can locate examples by looking through the docs:</p>
    <img style="width: 150px;" src="http://www.elevationacademy.co/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Screen-Shot-2016-03-09-at-7.16.12-PM.png">

    <p>All we have to do is add another class!</p>
    <pre style="background:#000;color:#f8f8f8"><span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;<span style="color:#89bdff">nav</span> <span style="color:#89bdff">class</span>=<span style="color:#65b042">"navbar navbar-default navbar-fixed-top"</span>></span>
<span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;/<span style="color:#89bdff">nav</span>></span>
</pre>
    
