  <div class="topic">
    <h4>Buttons</h4>
    <p>A quick word about buttons. Bootstrap offers so great default code for styling buttons. Check it out <a href="http://getbootstrap.com/css/#buttons">here</a>. Add the following HTML under the <c>intro-heading</c> div in your <c>header</c>:</p>

    <pre style="background:#000;color:#f8f8f8">&lt;<span style="color:#cda869">button</span> class="btn btn-primary">Tell Me More&lt;/<span style="color:#cda869">button</span>></pre>

    <p>Giving a link or a button the bootstrap class <c>btn</c> will make it look "bootsrappy". By adding additonal classes (<c>btn-primary</c>, <c>btn-success</c>, <c>btn-danger</c>) we can give our buttons more meaning.</p>
  </div>

