  <div class="topic">
    <h4>The Grid System!!!</h4>
    <p>If we look back up at the "services" page, we notice a 3 column grid. This is possibly Bootstrap's greatest advantage and achievement. Layout is hard, but not with Bootstrap. Take a mintue with your partner to checkout the <a href="http://getbootstrap.com/css/#grid" target="_blank">grid system</a> page here.</p>

    <p>To summarize, Bootstrap built it's grid off a "12-column grid" (like we did with ours). The rest can be summed up by these 3 bullets:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>Rows must be placed within a <c>.container (fixed-width)</c> or <c>.container-fluid (full-width)</c> for proper alignment and padding.<li>
      <li>Use rows to create horizontal groups of columns.</li>
      <li>Content should be placed within columns, and only columns may be immediate children of rows.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>In english, here are some good and bad examples:</p>

    <p>Good:</p>
    <pre style="background:#000;color:#f8f8f8"><span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;<span style="color:#89bdff">div</span> <span style="color:#89bdff">class</span>=<span style="color:#65b042">"container"</span>></span>
  <span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;<span style="color:#89bdff">div</span> <span style="color:#89bdff">class</span>=<span style="color:#65b042">"row"</span>></span>
    <span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;<span style="color:#89bdff">div</span> <span style="color:#89bdff">class</span>=<span style="color:#65b042">"col-md-8"</span>></span>.col-md-8<span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;/<span style="color:#89bdff">div</span>></span>
    <span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;<span style="color:#89bdff">div</span> <span style="color:#89bdff">class</span>=<span style="color:#65b042">"col-md-4"</span>></span>.col-md-4<span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;/<span style="color:#89bdff">div</span>></span>
  <span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;/<span style="color:#89bdff">div</span>></span>
<span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;/<span style="color:#89bdff">div</span>></span>
</pre>

    <p>Bad (no container):</p>
    <pre style="background:#000;color:#f8f8f8"><span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;<span style="color:#89bdff">div</span> <span style="color:#89bdff">class</span>=<span style="color:#65b042">"row"</span>></span>
  <span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;<span style="color:#89bdff">div</span> <span style="color:#89bdff">class</span>=<span style="color:#65b042">"col-md-6"</span>></span>.col-md-6<span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;/<span style="color:#89bdff">div</span>></span>
  <span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;<span style="color:#89bdff">div</span> <span style="color:#89bdff">class</span>=<span style="color:#65b042">"col-md-6"</span>></span>.col-md-6<span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;/<span style="color:#89bdff">div</span>></span>
<span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;/<span style="color:#89bdff">div</span>></span>
</pre>

    <p>Bad (no rows):</p>
    <pre style="background:#000;color:#f8f8f8"><span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;<span style="color:#89bdff">div</span> <span style="color:#89bdff">class</span>=<span style="color:#65b042">"col-md-4"</span>></span>.col-md-4<span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;/<span style="color:#89bdff">div</span>></span>
<span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;<span style="color:#89bdff">div</span> <span style="color:#89bdff">class</span>=<span style="color:#65b042">"col-md-4"</span>></span>.col-md-4<span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;/<span style="color:#89bdff">div</span>></span>
<span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;<span style="color:#89bdff">div</span> <span style="color:#89bdff">class</span>=<span style="color:#65b042">"col-md-4"</span>></span>.col-md-4<span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;/<span style="color:#89bdff">div</span>></span>

<span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;<span style="color:#89bdff">div</span> <span style="color:#89bdff">class</span>=<span style="color:#65b042">"col-md-6"</span>></span>.col-md-6<span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;/<span style="color:#89bdff">div</span>></span>
<span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;<span style="color:#89bdff">div</span> <span style="color:#89bdff">class</span>=<span style="color:#65b042">"col-md-6"</span>></span>.col-md-6<span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;/<span style="color:#89bdff">div</span>></span>
</pre>

    <p>What's wrong with leaving out the rows or containers? Remember our float problem and how we solved it with this code yesterday?</p>

    <pre style="background:#000;color:#f8f8f8"><span style="color:#9b703f">.row</span><span style="color:#89bdff">:before</span> {
  <span style="color:#c5af75">display</span>: table;
  <span style="color:#c5af75">content</span>: <span style="color:#65b042">""</span>;
}

<span style="color:#9b703f">.row</span><span style="color:#89bdff">:after</span> {
  <span style="color:#c5af75">display</span>: table;
  <span style="color:#c5af75">content</span>: <span style="color:#65b042">""</span>;
  <span style="color:#c5af75">clear</span>: <span style="color:#f9ee98">both</span>;
} 
</pre>
    
    <p>This is the <em>exact</em> code the Bootstrap uses to solve the float problem. Without it, we'd have a float problem because our columns are all floated. Whatever floats your boat, right?</p>
