    <p class="ex">4 * 3 is 12! So we used <c>col-md-4</c>... It looks a whole lot our framework, right? Except for the <c>md</c>. Bootstap has 4 columns tyeps: <c>xs</c>, <c>sm</c>, <c>md</c> and <c>lg</c>. This doesn't refer to the actual size of the columns but to how long the columns will stay side-by-side until they're stacked.</p>

    <p>For example, the <c>xs</c> columns will never stack no matter how small the screen is. But there's a media query at 970px that stacks the <c>md</c> columns so they be seen more easily on smaller screen.</p>
